  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate which combination therapy is more effective for
      improving the blood pressure (BP) and AM central SBP in hypertensive patients:Angiotensin II
      receptor blocker (ARB) plus calcium channel blocker (CCB) or ARB plus diuretics
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
